==Ancient Greek==
===Verb===
'''λέγω'''
# To [[say]], [[speak]].
===Conjugation===
Bold Forms are insubstantiated, see [[Talk:λέγω|talk page]].  Λέγω uses the verb εἶπον for all tenses except present and imperfect.  Εἶπον is actually the past tense of an obselete word and has been combined into λέγω's grammatical structure in a process known as [[w:suppletion|suppletion]], similar to [[go]] and [[went]] in English.  Also, it should be noted that εἶπον sometimes alternates between 1st and 2nd aorist endings, resulting in alternate forms, such as εἶπον and εἶπα for the 1st singular active indicative.  
